- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as microservices are a distributed computing architecture. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is relevant as the paper discusses issues and benefits of migrating to microservices, which is a software development topic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses technical anti-patterns in microservices, which could be related to programming languages. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on digital libraries or information retrieval.
